<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>Blessed is He Who hath revealed unto His slave the Criterion ( of right and wrong ), that he may be a warner to the peoples.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>He unto Whom belongeth the sovereignty of the heavens and the earth. He hath chosen no son nor hath He any partner. in the sovereignty. He hath created everything and hath meted out for it a measure.<?php break;}
case 3:{?>Yet they choose beside Him other gods who create naught but are themselves created, and possess not hurt nor profit for themselves, and possess not death nor life, nor power to raise the dead.<?php break;}
case 4:{?>Those who disbelieve say : This is naught but a lie that he hath invented, and other folk have helped him with it, so that they have produced a slander and a lie.<?php break;}
case 5:{?>And they say : Fables of the men of old which he hath had written down so that they are dictated to him morn and evening.<?php break;}
case 6:{?>Say ( unto them, O Muhammad ) : He Who knoweth the secret of the heavens and the earth hath revealed it. Lo! He ever is Forgiving, Merciful.<?php break;}
case 7:{?>And they say : What aileth this messenger ( of Allah ) that he eateth food and walketh in the markets? Why is not an angel sent down unto him, to be a warner with him.<?php break;}
case 8:{?>Or ( why is not ) a treasure thrown down unto him, or why hath he not a paradise from whence to eat? And the evildoers say : Ye are but following a man bewitched.<?php break;}
case 9:{?>See how they coin similitudes for thee, so that they are all astray and cannot find a road!<?php break;}
case 10:{?>Blessed is He Who, if He will, will assign thee better than ( all ) that. Gardens underneath which rivers flow, and will assign thee mansions.<?php break;}
case 11:{?>Nay, but they deny ( the coming of ) the Hour, and for those who deny ( the coming of ) the Hour We have prepared a Same.<?php break;}
case 12:{?>When it seeth them from afar, they bear the cracking and the roar thereof.<?php break;}
case 13:{?>And when they are Sung into a narrow place thereof, chained together, they pray for destruction there.<?php break;}
case 14:{?>Pray not that day for one destruction, but pray for many destructions!<?php break;}
case 15:{?>Say : Is that ( doom ) better or the Garden of Immortality which is promised unto those who ward off ( evil )? It will be their reward and journey ' s end.<?php break;}
case 16:{?>Therein abiding, they have all that they desire. It is for thy Lord a promise that must be fulfilled.<?php break;}
case 17:{?>And on the day when He will assemble them and that which they worship instead of Allah and will say : Was it ye who misled these my slaves or did they ( themselves ) wander from the way?<?php break;}
case 18:{?>They will say : Be Thou glorified! It was not for us to choose any protecting friends beside Thee; but Thou didst give them and their fathers ease till they forgot the warning and became lost folk<?php break;}
case 19:{?>Thus they will give you the lie regarding what ye say, then ye can neither avert ( the doom ) nor obtain help. And whoso among you doeth wrong, We shall make him taste great torment.<?php break;}
case 20:{?>We never sent before thee any messengers but lo! they ate food and walked in the markets. And We have appointed some of you a test for others : Will ye be steadfast? And thy Lord is ever Seer.<?php break;}
case 21:{?>And those who look not for a meeting with Us say : Why are angels not sent down unto us and ( why ) do we not see our Lord? Assuredly they think too highly of themselves and are scornful with great pride.<?php break;}
case 22:{?>On the day when they behold the angels, on that day there will be no good tidings for the guilty; and they will cry : A forbidding ban!<?php break;}
case 23:{?>And We shall turn unto the work they did and make it scattered motes.<?php break;}
case 24:{?>Those who have earned the Garden on that day will be better in their home and happier in their place of noonday rest;<?php break;}
case 25:{?>A day when the heaven with the clouds will be rent asunder and the angels will be sent down, a grand descent.<?php break;}
case 26:{?>The Sovereignty on that day will be the True ( Sovereignty ) belonging to the Beneficent One, and it will be a hard day for disbelievers.<?php break;}
case 27:{?>On the day when the wrongdoer gnaweth his hands, he will say : Ah, would that I had chosen a way together with the messenger ( of Allah )!<?php break;}
case 28:{?>Alas for me! Ah, would that I had never taken such an one for friend!<?php break;}
case 29:{?>He verily led me astray from the Reminder after it had reached me. Satan was ever man ' s deserter in the hour of need.<?php break;}
case 30:{?>And the messenger saith : O my Lord! Lo! mine own folk make this Quran of no account.<?php break;}
case 31:{?>Even so have We appointed unto every Prophet an opportent from among the guilty; but Allah sufficeth for a Guide and Helper.<?php break;}
case 32:{?>And those who disbelieve say : Why is the Quran not revealed unto him all at once? ( It is revealed ) thus that We may strengthen thy heart therewith; and We have arranged it in right order.<?php break;}
case 33:{?>And they bring thee no similitude but We bring thee the Truth ( as against it ), and better ( than their similitude ) as argument.<?php break;}
case 34:{?>Those who will be gathered on their faces unto Hell : such are worse in plight and further from the right road.<?php break;}
case 35:{?>We verify gave Moses the Scripture and placed with him his brother Aaron as henchman.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>Then We said : Go together unto the folk who have denied Our revelations. Then We destroyed them, a complete destruction.<?php break;}
case 37:{?>And Noah ' s folk, when they denied the messengers, We drowned them and made of them a portent for mankind We have prepared a painful doom for evil doers.<?php break;}
case 38:{?>And ( the tribes of ) Aad and Thamud, and the dwellers in Ar-Rass, and many generations in between.<?php break;}
case 39:{?>Each ( of them ) We warned by examples, and each ( of them ) We brought to utter ruin.<?php break;}
case 40:{?>And indeed they have passed by the township whereon was rained the fatal rain. Can it be that they have not seen it? Nay, but they hope for no resurrection.<?php break;}
case 41:{?>And when they see thee ( O Muhammad ) they treat thee only as a jest ( saying ) : Is this he whom Allah sendeth as a messenger?<?php break;}
case 42:{?>He would have led us far away from our gods if we had not been staunch to them. They will know, when they behold the doom, who is more astray as to the road.<?php break;}
case 43:{?>Hast thou seen him who chooseth for his god his own lust? Wouldst thou then be guardian over him?<?php break;}
case 44:{?>Or deemest thou that most of them hear or understand? They are but as the cattle, nay, but they are farther astray!<?php break;}
case 45:{?>Hast thou not seen how thy Lord hath spread the shade. And if He willed He could have made it still, then We have made the sun its pilot;<?php break;}
case 46:{?>Then We withdraw it unto Us, a gradual withdrawal?<?php break;}
case 47:{?>And He it is Who maketh night a covering for you, and sleep repose, and maketh day a resurrection.<?php break;}
case 48:{?>And He it is Who sendeth the winds, glad tidings heralding His mercy, and We send down purifying water from the sky.<?php break;}
case 49:{?>That We may give life thereby to a dead land, and We give many beasts and men that We have created to drink thereof.<?php break;}
case 50:{?>And verily We have repeated it among them that they may remember, but most of mankind begrudge aught save in gratitude.<?php break;}
case 51:{?>If We willed, We could raise up a warner in every village.<?php break;}
case 52:{?>So obey not the disbelievers, but strive against them herewith with a great endeavor.<?php break;}
case 53:{?>And He it is Who hath given independence to the two seas ( though they meet ); one palatable, sweet, and the other saltish, bitter; and hath set a bar and a forbidding ban between them.<?php break;}
case 54:{?>And He it is Who hath created man from water, and hath appointed for him kindred by blood and kindred by marriage; for thy Lord is ever Powerful.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>Yet they worship instead of Allah that which can neither benefit them nor hurt them. The disbeliever was ever a partisan against his Lord.<?php break;}
case 56:{?>And We have sent thee ( O Muhammad ) only as a bearer of good tidings and a warner.<?php break;}
case 57:{?>Say : I ask of you no reward for this, save that whoso will may choose a way unto his Lord.<?php break;}
case 58:{?>And trust thou in the Living One Who dieth not, and hymn His praise. He sufficeth as the Knower of His bondmen ' s sins,<?php break;}
case 59:{?>Who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them in six Days, then He mounted the Throne. The Beneficent! Ask any one informed concerning Him!<?php break;}
case 60:{?>And when it is said unto them: Prostrate to the Beneficent! they say: And what is the Beneficent? Are we to prostrate to whatever thou (Muhammad) biddest us? And it increaseth aversion in them.<?php break;}
case 61:{?>Blessed be He Who hath placed in the heaven mansions of the stars, and hath placed therein a great lamp and a moon giving light!<?php break;}
case 62:{?>And He it is Who hath appointed night and day in succession, for him who desireth to remember, or desireth thankfulness.<?php break;}
case 63:{?>The ( faithful ) slaves of the Beneficent are they who walk upon the earth modestly, and when the foolish ones address them answer : Peace;<?php break;}
case 64:{?>And who spend the night before their Lord, prostrate and standing,<?php break;}
case 65:{?>And who say : Our Lord! Avert from us the doom of hell; lo! the doom thereof is anguish;<?php break;}
case 66:{?>Lo! it is wretched as abode and station;<?php break;}
case 67:{?>And those who, when they spend, are neither prodigal nor grudging; and there is ever a firm station between the two;<?php break;}
case 68:{?>And those who cry not unto any other god along with Allah, nor take the life which Allah hath forbidden save in ( course of ) justice, nor commit adultery and whoso doeth this shall pay the penalty;<?php break;}
case 69:{?>The doom will be doubled for him on the Day of Resurrection, and he will abide therein disdained for ever;<?php break;}
case 70:{?>Save him who repenteth and believeth and doth righteous work; as for such, Allah will change their evil deeds to good deeds. Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.<?php break;}
case 71:{?>And whosoever repenteth and doeth good, he verily repenteth toward Allah with true repentance.<?php break;}
case 72:{?>And those who will not witness vanity, but when they pass near senseless play, pass by with dignity.<?php break;}
case 73:{?>And those who, when they are reminded of the revelations of their Lord, fall not deaf and blind thereat.<?php break;}
case 74:{?>And who say : Our Lord! Vouchsafe us comfort of our wives and of our offspring, and make us patterns for ( all ) those who ward off ( evil ).<?php break;}
case 75:{?>They will be awarded the high place forasmuch as they were steadfast, and they will meet therein with welcome and the word of peace,<?php break;}
case 76:{?>Abiding there for ever. Happy is it as abode and station!<?php break;}
case 77:{?>Say ( O Muhammad, unto the disbelievers ) : My Lord would not concern himself with you but for your prayer. But now ye have denied ( the Truth ), therefor there will be judgment.<?php break;}
}?>